1335.name: NiCrCo 617
1335.Applications: NiCrCo 617 is a high temperature alloy which is used for welding of nickel-chromium-cobalt-molybdenum alloys (UNS Number N06617). This filler metal can also be used for overlay cladding where similar alloy is required such as gasturbines and ethylene equimpent.
1335.Suitable_For: Inconel alloys 600 and 601, Incoloy alloys 800 HT and 802 and cast alloys such as HK-40, HP and HP-45 Modified. UNS Number N06617, 2.4663, 1.4952, 1.4958, 1.4959, NiCr21Co12Mo, X6CrNiNbN 25 20, X5NiCrAlTi 31 20, X8NiCrAlTi 32 21, Alloy 617, N08810, N08811
